{% comment %}
  ===== FYXX CUSTOM: secondary "quick links" header nav + slim desktop menu =====

  Renders the compact quick-links menu (linklist 'secondary-menu-test':
  Home / Shop / Rewards) inline in the desktop header, and slims the main
  desktop navigation so the long 15-item menu no longer sprawls across the top.

  How the slim works: the theme already has a hamburger button
  (.site-nav__compress-menu) whose click handler always toggles the full nav
  row (.site-header__element--sub[data-type="nav"]) open/closed — it is just
  hidden by CSS until you scroll. We surface that hamburger at all times on
  desktop and hide the full nav row by default, so the quick-links become the
  primary visible desktop nav and the full menu is one tap away in the
  hamburger (and still in the drawer on mobile).

  Originally authored by NAIM on the previous (8.0.0) theme as the
  'custom.secondary-menu-header' snippet; migrated + cleaned up for 9.1.0.
  To revert: delete this snippet and remove its {% render %} hook in
  snippets/section.header.liquid.
{% endcomment %}

<style>
  /* --- Quick links --- */
  .secondary-menu {
    display: none; /* hidden on mobile; full menu lives in the mobile drawer there */
    align-items: center;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-right: 1rem;
  }

  .secondary-menu ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: 18px;
  }

  .secondary-menu li {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .secondary-menu a {
    color: #ffffff;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: var(--element-text-font-size--body-md);
    padding: 5px 8px;
    display: block;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .secondary-menu a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media only screen and (min-width: 769px) {
    .secondary-menu {
      display: flex;
    }

    /* --- Slim desktop nav ---
       Keep the hamburger trigger visible at all times (it normally only
       appears once the header compresses on scroll), and hide the full menu
       row until the hamburger toggles it open. */
    .header-layout[data-nav='below'] .header-item--compress-nav {
      visibility: visible;
      opacity: 1;
      width: auto;
      transform: none;
    }

    .site-header__element--sub[data-type='nav']:not(.is-active) {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>

{% if linklists['secondary-menu-test'].links.size > 0 %}
  <nav class="secondary-menu" role="navigation" aria-label="Secondary menu">
    <ul>
      {% for link in linklists['secondary-menu-test'].links %}
        <li>
          <a href="{{ link.url }}">{{ link.title }}</a>
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </nav>
{% endif %}
{% comment %} ===== END FYXX CUSTOM ===== {% endcomment %}
